    <p>If any of these apply, book before you light the next fire:</p>
    <div class="reason-grid">
      <div class="rc"><span class="rc-icon">&#128293;</span><div class="rc-title">Smoke coming back in</div><div class="rc-desc">Restricted flue from creosote buildup. Very common in the Ranges where heaters run hard all winter.</div></div>
      <div class="rc"><span class="rc-icon">&#129440;</span><div class="rc-title">Creosote or tar buildup</div><div class="rc-desc">Long cold winters and sustained heavy use mean faster accumulation. Annual cleaning is essential here.</div></div>
      <div class="rc"><span class="rc-icon">&#128038;</span><div class="rc-title">Bird or possum nesting</div><div class="rc-desc">Unused flues over summer are prime nesting spots. Check before the first fire of the season.</div></div>
      <div class="rc"><span class="rc-icon">&#127810;</span><div class="rc-title">Pre-season service</div><div class="rc-desc">Book in March or April before the cold hits — we fill up fast once the Ranges season begins.</div></div>
    </div>
  </section>

